The `test-and-set` is an **atomic hardware instruction** used to write to a memory location and return its old value as a single, indivisible operation.

```c
boolean test_and_set(boolean *target) {
    boolean rv = *target;
    *target = TRUE;
    return rv;
}
```

If multiple threads try to execute it simultaneously, the hardware guarantees only one executes it at a time. It's the building block of spinlocks and mutexes to solve critical section problems.
